| FalkorDB image SHA | `falkordb/falkordb@sha256:e93fcd753fe612fb0a222166a0620a1ae31b826a12f223c3b6d06038d9d7a364` (human tag: `v4.2.0`; Redis 8.6.3; image dated 2026-05-14) | `installer/falkordb.pin` |
| Ubuntu runner image | `ubuntu-24.04` — glibc 2.39; covers Ubuntu 24.04+, Debian 13+, Fedora 39+, RHEL 10+. **Revised from `ubuntu-22.04` on first CI run** (2026-06-13): ag's `onnx` feature pulls `ort` crate's prebuilt ONNX binaries which require glibc 2.39, so 22.04 was never actually viable. | `.github/workflows/release.yml` (`runs-on: ubuntu-24.04`) |
| Semver starting version | `v0.1.0`. No pre-release tags (`-alpha` / `-beta` / `-rc`) — iterate `0.1.0 → 0.1.1 → 0.1.2 → … → 0.x.0 → 1.0.0`. `v1.0.0` only when Phase H acceptance is met. | `Cargo.toml` workspace `version` + `installer/Cargo.toml` |
| GitHub Releases publish mode | **Public** from day one with `prerelease=true` on every tag before `v1.0.0`. Lets early testers discover and report; the auto-update channel policy can correctly filter stable vs pre-release. | repo settings + `release.yml` step `gh release create … --prerelease` |
| `.desktop` `Categories=` and `MimeType=` | `Categories=Development;Database;`. **No `MimeType=`** — ag ingests through the web UI, not OS file association. Skipped `Office` / `Education` / `Science` as misleading. | `installer/assets/ag-installer.desktop` |
| Auto-update channel policy | Stable-only default: GET `https://api.github.com/repos/<owner>/<repo>/releases/latest` (excludes pre-releases by definition). Opt-in `--include-prereleases` flag polls `/releases` and filters `draft=false`. Cache result in `~/.cache/ag-installer/last-check.json` for 4 hours. | `installer/src/update_check.rs` |

**Outcome:** every following phase can start without re-litigating
these. The `installer/` paths above are referenced but not yet
written — Phase A creates the crate skeleton and lays these files
down with the values from this table.

