### Phase E — First-run config (week 5)

<details>
<summary>Tasks · Risks · Acceptance · End-of-phase commit</summary>


**Goal:** Screen 5 collects Ollama model, FalkorDB password, agent
mode; writes the env file; starts ag.service.

**Tasks:**

1. Implement `installer/src/first_run.rs`:
   - `pub async fn probe_ollama_models() -> Result<Vec<String>>`
     — GETs `http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags`, parses model names
   - `pub fn write_first_run_settings(env_path: &Path, choices: &FirstRunChoices) -> Result<()>`
     — atomic write: read existing ag.env, replace lines for the
     keys in scope, write to temp + rename
   - `pub async fn change_falkordb_password(new: &str) -> Result<()>`
     — re-render falkordb.service.tmpl, `daemon-reload`,
     `restart falkordb.service`, verify with ping
2. First-Run form UI:
   - Ollama model dropdown (disabled with a hint if no models)
   - Password input with toggle-visible
   - Agent mode dropdown with per-option description
3. "Start ag now" button:
   - Calls `systemctl --user start ag.service`
   - Polls `/health` up to 20s
   - Transitions to Done screen on success
   - Shows in-form error if `/health` doesn't come up

**Dependencies:** Phase D complete.

**Risks:**
- Atomic env file writes are fiddly with newline preservation and
  comments. Test against `.env.example` to make sure the file remains
  readable after modification.
- FalkorDB password change while the service is running: depends on
  whether redis-server reloads `--requirepass` on restart. It does,
  but the running connections need to be drained. Acceptable since
  ag.service isn't started yet at this point.

**Acceptance:**
- On a fresh VM with Ollama running, the dropdown lists the user's
  models; default selection lands in ag.env
- Changing the FalkorDB password restarts the unit and `redis-cli
  ping` with the new password returns PONG
- "Start ag now" lights up the Done screen with `/health: 200`

**End-of-phase commit:** `feat(installer): first-run config — Ollama
model, FalkorDB password, agent mode`.

</details>

